trans-unit.source: Represents a window that supports content navigation.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma janela que dá suporte à navegação de conteúdo.

trans-unit.source: NavigationWindow derives from <xref:System.Windows.Window> and extends it with the ability to navigate to and display content.
trans-unit.target: NavigationWindow deriva <xref:System.Windows.Window>e estende a capacidade de navegar e exibir o conteúdo.</xref:System.Windows.Window>

trans-unit.source: Content can be any [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] object or [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] file.
trans-unit.target: O conteúdo pode ser qualquer [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] objeto ou [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] arquivo.

trans-unit.source: In general, however, a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page> object is the preferred way to package content for navigation.
trans-unit.target: Em geral, no entanto, um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>objeto é a melhor maneira de conteúdo do pacote para navegação.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>

trans-unit.source: Content can be navigated to by setting the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A> property with the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] for the desired content.
trans-unit.target: Conteúdo pode ser navegado, definindo o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>propriedade com o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] para o conteúdo desejado.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>

trans-unit.source: Additionally, content can be navigated to by using one of the following overloads of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A> method: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%29> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29> When content is navigated to by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationWindow will return an object that contains the content.
trans-unit.target: Além disso, conteúdo pode ser navegado usando uma das sobrecargas de seguir a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>método:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%29>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29>ao conteúdo é navegado por [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationWindow retornará um objeto que contém o conteúdo.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Uri%29> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Navigation by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] also supports navigation to a content fragment.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Navegação por [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] também oferece suporte à navegação para um fragmento de conteúdo.

trans-unit.source: See <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation>.
trans-unit.target: Consulte <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation>

trans-unit.source: Alternatively, content can be navigated to by using one of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A> method overloads that accepts an object: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%29> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29> The lifetime of a navigation can be tracked through the following events: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigating> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigated> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationProgress> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationStopped> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.LoadCompleted> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation>.
trans-unit.target: Como alternativa, conteúdo pode ser acessado usando um do <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>sobrecargas do método que aceita um objeto:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%29>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29>o tempo de vida de uma navegação pode ser controlado por meio de eventos a seguir:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigating>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigated>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationProgress>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationStopped>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.LoadCompleted>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.FragmentNavigation> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.LoadCompleted> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationStopped> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationFailed> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.NavigationProgress> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigated> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigating> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%28System.Object%29> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: Not all events are raised each time that a navigation occurs; the set of events that are raised is determined by the type of navigation that occurs (content or content fragment) and how the navigation completes (canceled, stopped, or failed).
trans-unit.target: Nem todos os eventos são gerados sempre que ocorra uma navegação; o conjunto de eventos que são gerados é determinado pelo tipo de navegação que ocorre (fragmento de conteúdo ou conteúdo) e como a navegação é concluída (cancelada, interrompido ou falha).

trans-unit.source: The following figure illustrates the sequence in which these events will fire: ![Page navigation flow chart](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "Page navigation flow chart") During or after a navigation, NavigationWindow provides information about the content that is being navigated to, including the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the content being navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>), the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the current content (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CurrentSource%2A>), and an object that contains the content that was navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>).
trans-unit.target: A figura a seguir ilustra a sequência na qual esses eventos acionarão: ![gráfico de fluxo de navegação de página](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "gráfico de fluxo de navegação de página") durante ou após uma navegação, NavigationWindow fornece informações sobre o conteúdo que está sendo navegado, incluindo o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo que está sendo navegado (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>), o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo atual (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CurrentSource%2A>) e um objeto que contém o conteúdo que foi direcionado (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CurrentSource%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>

trans-unit.source: When content is navigated to, NavigationWindow records the navigation as an entry in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Quando o conteúdo é navegar até, NavigationWindow registra a navegação como uma entrada no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to back navigation history when either a new navigation occurs, by calling the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A> method, or by navigating to an entry in forward navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoForward%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada para fazer o histórico de navegação quando ocorre uma nova navegação, chamando o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>método, ou navegando para uma entrada no histórico de navegação de avanço, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoForward%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoForward%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to forward navigation history by navigating to an entry in back navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoBack%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada ao histórico de navegação de avanço, navegando para uma entrada no histórico de navegação, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoBack%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.GoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoBack%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoForward%2A> report whether there are entries in back and forward navigation history, respectively.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoBack%2A>e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoForward%2A>relatar se há entradas no e o histórico de navegação de avanço, respectivamente.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoForward%2A></xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.CanGoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: The first time that one piece of content is navigated to from another piece of content, NavigationWindow automatically displays a navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] that allows users to navigate back and forwards through navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Na primeira vez que uma parte do conteúdo é acessada de outro item de conteúdo, NavigationWindow exibe automaticamente uma navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] que permite aos usuários navegar de volta e encaminha no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: You can configure when the navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] is shown by setting the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.ShowsNavigationUI%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Você pode configurar quando a navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] é mostrado, definindo a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.ShowsNavigationUI%2A>propriedade.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.ShowsNavigationUI%2A>

trans-unit.source: The most recent entry in back navigation history can be removed by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: A entrada mais recente no histórico de navegação pode ser removida chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.RemoveBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationWindow does not store an instance of a content object in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: NavigationWindow não armazene uma instância de um objeto de conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Instead, NavigationWindow creates a new instance of the content object each time it is navigated to by using navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Em vez disso, NavigationWindow cria uma nova instância do objeto conteúdo de cada vez que ele é para onde navegar usando o histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: This behavior is designed to avoid excessive memory consumption when large numbers and large pieces of content are being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Esse comportamento é projetado para evitar o consumo excessivo de memória quando grandes números e grandes partes do conteúdo estão sendo navegados.

trans-unit.source: Consequently, the state of the content is not remembered from one navigation to the next.
trans-unit.target: Consequentemente, o estado do conteúdo não será lembrado na barra de uma navegação para a próxima.

trans-unit.source: However, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] provides several techniques by which you can store a piece of state for a piece of content in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] oferece várias técnicas que você pode armazenar uma parte do estado de uma parte do conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Using <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.AddBackEntry%2A>, you can also remember multiple sets of state for a single page instance.
trans-unit.target: Usando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.AddBackEntry%2A>, lembre-se também vários conjuntos de estado para uma instância única página.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.AddBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationWindow is one of two navigators in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], the other being <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: NavigationWindow é um dos dois navegadores na [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], outro <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: Essentially, navigator is a class supports navigation and navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Essencialmente, o navegador é que uma classe dá suporte à navegação e o histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Visually, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] use [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] as a navigator, to provide an integrated user experience.
trans-unit.target: Visualmente, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] usar [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] como um navegador, para fornecer uma experiência de usuário integrada.

trans-unit.source: However, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] actually use NavigationWindow as the navigator; the <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A> property of an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] running in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] will return a reference to the NavigationWindow, and the navigation history that is managed by the NavigationWindow is integrated with the navigation history that is managed by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: No entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] realmente usar NavigationWindow como o navegador; o <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A>propriedade de um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] em execução em [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] retornará uma referência a NavigationWindow, e o histórico de navegação que é gerenciado pelo NavigationWindow é integrado com o histórico de navegação que é gerenciado pelo [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)].</xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A>

trans-unit.source: **Content Model:** NavigationWindow is a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>, which means that NavigationWindow can contain content such as text, images, or panels.
trans-unit.target: **Modelo de conteúdo:** NavigationWindow é um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>, que significa que NavigationWindow pode conter conteúdo como texto, imagens ou painéis.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl>

trans-unit.source: Also, NavigationWindow is a root element and, consequently, cannot be part of another element's content.
trans-unit.target: Além disso, NavigationWindow é um elemento raiz e, consequentemente, não pode ser parte de outro conteúdo de elemento.

trans-unit.source: For more information about the content model for <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button>, see [WPF Content Model](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações sobre o modelo de conteúdo para <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button>, consulte [modelo de conteúdo do WPF](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button>

trans-unit.source: Customizing the NavigationWindow Control To apply the same property settings to multiple NavigationWindow controls, use the <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Style%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Personalizando controle NavigationWindow para aplicar as mesmas configurações de propriedade para vários controles de NavigationWindow, use o <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Style%2A>propriedade.</xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Style%2A>

trans-unit.source: You can modify the default <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate> to give the control a unique appearance.
trans-unit.target: Você pode modificar o padrão <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>para que o controle uma aparência exclusiva.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>

trans-unit.source: For more information about creating a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>, see [Customizing the Appearance of an Existing Control by Creating a ControlTemplate](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações sobre como criar um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>, consulte [Personalizando a aparência de um controle existente, criando um ControlTemplate](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ControlTemplate>

trans-unit.source: To see the parts and states that are specific to the NavigationWindow, see [NavigationWindow Styles and Templates](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Para ver as partes e os estados que são específicos para o NavigationWindow, consulte [NavigationWindow estilos e modelos](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: If a property is set by a default style, the property might change from its default value when the control appears in the application.
trans-unit.target: Se uma propriedade é definida por um estilo padrão, a propriedade pode ser alterada de seu valor padrão quando o controle é exibido no aplicativo.

trans-unit.source: The default style is determined by which desktop theme is used when the application is running.
trans-unit.target: O estilo padrão é determinado pelo qual tema de área de trabalho é usado quando o aplicativo está em execução.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Default WPF Themes](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=158252).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações, consulte [padrão WPF temas](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=158252).

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a value that indicates whether a <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow"></xref> isolates external [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xaml-md.md)] content within a partial trust security sandbox (with default Internet zone permission set).

trans-unit.source: External content is [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] content that is not included with an application as either a resource file or a content file (for more information, see [WPF Application Resource, Content, and Data Files](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)).
trans-unit.target: Conteúdo externo é [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] conteúdo que não está incluído com um aplicativo como um arquivo de recurso ou um arquivo de conteúdo (para obter mais informações, consulte [recursos de aplicativo do WPF, conteúdo e arquivos de dados](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)).

trans-unit.source: When SandboxExternalContent is true, and the content of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> is an external [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] file, the content is loaded into a partial trust security sandbox that is limited to the default Internet zone permission set.
trans-unit.target: Quando SandboxExternalContent é verdadeiro e o conteúdo do <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>é externo [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] arquivo, o conteúdo é carregado em uma proteção de segurança de confiança parcial é limitada ao padrão conjunto de permissões de zona da Internet.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: Additionally, the external content is loaded into a separate process.
trans-unit.target: Além disso, o conteúdo externo é carregado em um processo separado.

trans-unit.source: Consequently, the external content becomes isolated and does not have access to application-scope resources, such as resource dictionaries (for more information, see <xref:System.Windows.ResourceDictionary>).
trans-unit.target: Consequentemente, o conteúdo externo fica isolado e não tem acesso a recursos de escopo do aplicativo, como dicionários de recursos (para obter mais informações, consulte <xref:System.Windows.ResourceDictionary>).</xref:System.Windows.ResourceDictionary>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> contains external content only when the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A> property is set to the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] for an external [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] file.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>contém conteúdo externo somente quando o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A>estiver definida como o [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] para externo [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] arquivo.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow.Source%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> content that is provided using the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A> property is considered internal content and, subsequently, is not isolated.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>conteúdo que é fornecido usando o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A>propriedade é considerada conteúdo interno e, subsequentemente, não é isolada.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.ContentControl.Content%2A></xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>
